In a bid to better equip participants with an in-depth knowledge of core business principles, problem-solving capabilities, analytical competencies, and contemporary business models that are needed to thrive within the 21st-century business ecosystem, a Boston-based business school, Tekedia Institute, has announced the launch of its virtual professional Mini-MBA programme for young professionals and business leaders.   CSO to access effect of COVID-19 pandemic on mental health…     Corruption: FG urged to inculcate spirituality in tertiary…     Ugwu joins presidential race, urges North to concede ticket…   The 12-week innovative management programme is  designed to provide practical training on business growth, optimization, and execution. It is on this backdrop that faculty members have been selected from global organisations like Microsoft, Shell, Flutterwave, Nigerian Breweries, Jobberman, Coca Cola, Deloitte, Schlumberger, Mastercard, Access Bank, AXA Mansard, KPMG, MTN Nigeria, amongst others to provide contemporary insights into global best business practices.